T*
(make steady progress, get support from mentors and peers, and create tangible, public-facing) Tj
T*
(work you can actually show future employers. Hack Your Summer is partly a reaction to the) Tj
T*
(internship crisis facing US college students this year. There are way fewer available) Tj
T*
(internships than usual, as companies have reduced their hiring ambitions and teams have less) Tj
T*
(capacity to coach interns. Hack Your Summer provides an alternative path for the many students) Tj
T*
(who didn't catch one of those rare internships. A second \(free\) cohort starts on July 13th, and) Tj
T*
(the deadline for students to apply is July 8th. They're also accepting volunteers to help) Tj
